Moscow Treaty on Strategic Offensive Reductions The Moscow Treaty on Strategic Offensive Reductions is a treaty between the United States of America and the Russian Federation to further reduce strategic offensive arms. The treaty was signed on 24 May 2002 at Moscow and entered into force on 1 June 2003. The treaty called for the reduction of the number of operationally deployed strategic nuclear warheads to between 1700 and 2200 by December 31, 2012.
